quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  11,82,"When Our command came, We turned that town upside down and We rained upon it stones of clay, layer upon layer"
  11,83,marked for them by the decree of your Lord. The punishment of the unjust was not far off
  11,84,"To the people of Midian, We sent their brother Shu'ayb. He said, \"My people, worship God. You have no deity other than Him. Do not give short measure and short weight. I see you are prospering. I fear for you the punishment of a fateful Day"
  11,85,"O my people, [always] give full measure and weight, in all fairness and do not defraud people by making short delivery, and do not spread corruption in the land"
  11,86,"What God leaves with you is the best for you, if you are believers. I have not been appointed as your keeper"
  11,87,"They said, \"Shu'ayb, does your prayer tell you that we should abandon what our forefathers worshipped and that we should stop disposing of our belongings as we please? You are indeed the only wise and rightly-guided man"
  11,88,"[Shu'ayb] said, \"O my people! What do you think? If I have clear evidence from my Lord, and He has sustained me with fair sustenance from Himself [should I not guide you?]. I have no desire to do, out of opposition to you, what I am asking you not to do. I only want to reform you as far as I can. Nor can I succeed without God's help. In Him I have put my trust and to Him I turn"